Please tag your friends, and share this video :) @hybridperformancemethod

node.text:
In 60 seconds you will finally understand how to estimate how many total calories you should consume to LOSE, GAIN or MAINTAIN your body weight.

Some more tips:
⚡️ aim to consume 1g of PROTEIN per lb of body weight MINIMUM
⚡️keep your grams of fat intake at 20-30% of total calories
⚡️go for a 10min walk after your meals
⚡️weigh yourself daily and take the average at the end of the week for a few weeks to asses whether or not you’re in the right track. ASSESS don’t GUESS

@hybridperformancemethod

node.text:
If you look at successful people and think to yourself, ⁠
⁠
“must be nice” …⁠
⁠
You truly have no idea.⁠
⁠
There is no such thing as an overnight success.⁠
⁠
There is no such thing as “she just got lucky.”⁠
⁠
There are no hand-outs.⁠
⁠
There are no shortcuts.⁠
⁠
Behind all of the PRs, the fancy cars, the dream body, the financial freedom, whatever your goal may be…⁠
⁠
Behind all of that is daily work.⁠
⁠
The mundane routines that don’t make it to the highlight reel.⁠
⁠
It’s about knowing how to make a habit out of your training, how to make a habit out of optimizing your nutrition, how to make a habit of pursuing personal growth in whatever form speaks most to you.⁠
⁠
It’s about getting out of your comfort zone and pushing past your limits. ⁠
⁠
It’s about telling your “all or nothing” mindset that it isn’t welcome here.⁠
⁠
It’s about finding a sustainable way to show up for yourself every single day.⁠
⁠
Are you up for the challenge? ⁠
⁠
Join me in our latest course...⁠
⁠
HYBRID Habits⁠
⁠
A self-paced online video course with downloadable workbook that will arm you with the tools to build the habits and systems you need to implement to transform your loftiest goals into reality.⁠
⁠
But if self-growth isn’t your thing and you don’t have time to unlock your potential, then hey... must be nice.⁠
⁠
Save your seat for the upcoming semester of HYBRID Habits today. ⁠
⁠
Remember, enrollment is only open for 2 weeks, so don’t miss your chance!⁠
⁠👇 ⁠⁠⁠👇 ⁠⁠⁠👇 ⁠⠀⁠⁠

www.hybridperformancemethod.com/courses⁠⠀⁠⁠

node.text:
The only reason I keep posting pictures like this…

Is because I support movements and trends in which women are able to create their own image of self and construct their own idea of femininity. While I recognize that such content opens the doors to comments that objectify women, I think it ultimately results in a net positive: empowerment.. Social media platforms are distinct from traditional media in that they give the user power.

Historically, women were solely consumers of media, now social media allow us to become independent creators of cultural content and self-construct our own gendered and sexual identities.

At the same time we should recognize the complexity of the construction of identity and not ignore its nuances. 
Because social media platforms are open to the public the original content of women embracing their sexuality and femininity can be transformed into sites of hostile surveillance via the male gaze. A duality of freedom and oppression that we need to take note of.

Let’s discuss 👇🏽 below.

node.text:
Fat isn’t making you gain weight and neither are carbs.

Your self control is.

It’s a lot easier to blame it on something or someone else than it is to take responsibility for your habits, environment and self discipline. Everyone wants to be great until they have to do what greatness requires.

When it comes to weight management, it’s simple. It’s about making small changes in your daily routine that you can consistently stick to for long periods of time. Long lasting body composition changes happen as a result of the average of your efforts over time.

Here’s where I would start:
1. Increase your protein intake to at least 1g per lb of body weight and spread it evenly throughout the day
2. Lift weights
3. Walk often 
4. Avoid drinking calories if you’re attempting to be in a calorie deficit
5. Consume a moderate amount of carbs and cycle them around your workouts if you’re in a deficit
6. Don’t be afraid of fat- it is not the enemy

For more guidance check out HYBRID NUTRITION @hybridperformancemethod
